sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Tyson Foods Inc (Symbol: TSN), where a total of 10,869 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 1.1 million underlying shares.
That amounts to about 43.5% of TSN's average daily trading volume over the past month of 2.5 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $56.50 strike put option expiring June 09, 2017 , with 1,285 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 128,500 underlying shares of TSN.

Below is a chart showing TSN's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $56.50 strike highlighted in orange:

Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) options are showing a volume of 13,076 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 1.3 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 43.4% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.0 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $85 strike put option expiring June 16, 2017 , with 1,892 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 189,200 underlying shares of CRM.

Below is a chart showing CRM's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $85 strike highlighted in orange:

And Microsoft Corporation (Symbol: MSFT) saw options trading volume of 104,052 contracts, representing approximately 10.4 million underlying shares or approximately 42.8% of MSFT's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 24.3 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $69 strike call option expiring May 12, 2017 , with 26,779 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.7 million underlying shares of MSFT.
